node.text:
Starbucks' fall menu debuts today in the US and Canada! The Pumpkin Spice Latte and Pumpkin Cream Cold Brew return along with a new Apple Crisp Macchiato. The macchiato can be made iced or hot and features apple brown sugar syrup and a spiced apple drizzle. Also returning are the pumpkin scone, pumpkin cream cheese muffin, and pumpkin loaf (well, that one is returning to Canada; it's available year-round in the US). 

News and images via Starbucks.

node.text:
Incogmeato and Eggo are hosting a giveaway tomorrow for National Waffle Day! They have partnered to create new Chik'n & Waffle packs featuring Eggo waffles and Incogmeato chik'n strips. The pack also has recipe ideas like Honey Butter Chik'n & Waffles and Sriracha Chik'n & Waffles. Head on over to incogmeato.com/eggo tomorrow, August 24, at 11 am Eastern to enter for a free pack!

Thanks to Kellogg's for the news and images!

node.text:
Now here's something different! Candy & Snack Today reported that Raspberry & Rose Ritter Sport bars will be out in the US for the Valentine's season. No, not rosé like the wine, rose like the flower. The bar contains milk chocolate and a raspberry creme filling with raspberry pieces and rose oil. 

I hope this leads to more seasonal Ritter Sport bars for the US. The brand does not have nearly the same traction here as it does in Germany and the rest of Europe. I would love to see Ritter Sport's popularity increase outside Europe.

News via Candy & Snack Today. Image via Candy & Snack Today and Euro-American Brands.

node.text:
The new Apple Cider Donut Oreos officially launch today! I found them at Walmart.

The Oreos are more apple-forward than an apple cider donut, and that's fine by me! The flavor is a mix of apple and cinnamon. They're pretty darn tasty and worth picking up a pack.
